This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test suite. Every production method is called (→ 95% coverage) but almost nothing is verified. Here's the severity-ranked audit:

---

## 🔴 Critical — Assertion-Free Tests (Coverage Inflation)

**4 tests have zero assertions.** They can never fail unless an exception is thrown.

| Test | Bug it would miss |
|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` (L17-21) | `Save()` silently drops the product — test still green |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33-36) | Price not actually updated — test still green |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` (L39-43) | Product still exists after remove — test still green |
| `GetProductCount_Works` (L63-66) | Returns wrong count — test still green |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L68-74) | Prices unchanged after discount — test still green |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L84-88) | Products never persisted — test still green |

**Fix pattern:**
```csharp
// AddProduct_Works → verify round-trip
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var retrieved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", retrieved?.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, retrieved?.Price);

// UpdatePrice_Works → verify new price
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")?.Price);

// RemoveProduct_Works → verify deletion
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));

// GetProductCount_Works → verify count value
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
Assert.AreEqual(1, _catalog.GetProductCount());

// ApplyBulkDiscount_Works → verify discounted prices
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")?.Price);  // 9.99 * 0.9

// ImportFromCsv_Works → verify imported product
_catalog.ImportFromCsv("SKU-001,Widget,9.99");
var p = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", p?.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, p?.Price);
```

---

## 🟠 High — `Assert.IsNotNull`-Only Tests (Shallow Assertions)

**3 tests** call `Assert.IsNotNull` but never check the returned *values*. A method could return the wrong product, wrong results, or garbage CSV — the test passes.

| Test | What's unchecked |
|---|---|
| `GetProduct_Works` (L23-29) | SKU, Name, Price of the returned product |
| `SearchProducts_Works` (L45-52) | Result count, contents, that non-matches are excluded |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` (L77-82) | CSV format, field values, line count |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` (L55-60) | Collection count and contents |

**Fix pattern:**
```csharp
// GetProduct_Works → verify identity
var result = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual("SKU-001", result?.Sku);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", result?.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, result?.Price);

